history.content: It’s two technicals for your major. So a class like EPS wouldn’t count (ex: for an EECS major)

Hi All,

The COE website defines technical courses as "courses in engineering, computer science, data science, math, statistics, chemistry, the physical sciences, or the biological sciences". Does this include courses in the Department of Earth and Planetary Science, specifically EPS 130 - Seismology? I would like to know to make sure I fulfill my 2 tech requirement. Thanks!

Edit: sorry if this is a dumb question -- I know that probably it is included under the umbrella of "physical sciences", but just wanted to be completely sure.
history.subject: Are EPS classes considered technical courses?
